# Dotfiles Core

Read [CLAUDE.md](../../CLAUDE.md) for full architecture. These rules are always in effect.

## Stow

- Symlink packages from `~/.dotfiles` with `stow <package>` — never `cp` or `ln` for package files
- Dry-run with `stow -n <package>` before manual stow changes

## Shell extension

- System RC files minimally source `~/.config/bash/` or `~/.config/zsh/` (via ZDOTDIR)
- Only `setup_bash()` and `setup_zsh()` modify system `~/.bashrc`, `~/.bash_profile`, `~/.zshenv`
- Tool setup functions check prerequisites and detect conflicts; they do not append init lines dynamically

## Theme

Synthwave 2077 palette for new UI configs:

- Pink `#ff7edb`, Purple `#b893ce`, Cyan `#72f1b8`, Neon green `#fede5d`

## Commits

- No AI attribution in commit messages
- Only commit when the user explicitly asks
